the improvement over 3.1 version is visible.&nbsp;
The overall aesthetics are much better. The&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:01.440 --> 00:12:07.040
acting has improved and it's pretty good, too.&nbsp;
Two issues we spotted which are actually quite&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:07.040 --> 00:12:14.320
serious. Veo 4 on many occasions had a problem&nbsp;
with lip-sync and also didn't follow the prompt,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:14.320 --> 00:12:21.440
especially when we asked for slightly more&nbsp;
complex camera motion. One thing worth noting:&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:21.440 --> 00:12:28.960
the Omni function here is much more than just a&nbsp;
chance to use reference items. Veo 4 Omni offers a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:35.600
lot of additional editing functionalities like&nbsp;
iterative video editing with preserved content,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:35.600 --> 00:12:42.880
video remixing or conversational videography&nbsp;
direction. But at the end of the day, it all comes&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:42.880 --> 00:12:48.960
down to how good the outcome is, not how easy it&nbsp;
was to produce. As the audience doesn't care much&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:55.760
about the process, they care about the result. And&nbsp;
at least for now, nothing beats Seedance 2.0 &nbsp;&nbsp;

